{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the moderate within-group effect size for both groups, the between-group effect size was small (see Table 5).",
    "The between-group difference posttreatment was not significant in the regression analysis.",
    "Similarly, for anxiety, Kenter et al. [11] reported moderate within-group effect sizes (intervention group: Cohen's d =.41; control group:Cohen's d =.52) and small between-group effect size (see Table 5), and they found no significant difference between the intervention group and the control group.",
    "The clinical outcomes in Kolovos et al. [36] were the same as Kenter et al., [11] but Kolovos et al.",
    "focused on estimating the cost-effectiveness of the intervention in comparison with enhanced usual care."
  ]
}